# Library Management System — AI Agent Rules
# These rules apply to ALL AI coding assistants (Cursor, Claude, Copilot)

## MANDATORY RULES

### Architecture
- NEVER generate code that uses external databases (PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis, etc.)
- NEVER use external APIs or HTTP calls
- ALL data storage MUST use In-Memory collections (Python dict/list)
- ALWAYS program to interfaces (abstract base classes in src/storage/interfaces.py)
- NEVER bypass the Repository pattern — services talk ONLY through repository interfaces

### Code Quality
- NEVER generate a class without a corresponding abstract interface
- ALWAYS follow SOLID principles — especially Single Responsibility and Dependency Inversion
- NEVER create God classes — split responsibilities into focused classes
- ALWAYS use dependency injection in constructors
- NEVER use global state or singletons

### Testing (TDD)
- ALWAYS write tests before or simultaneously with implementation
- EVERY new service method MUST have at least 3 tests (happy path + 2 edge cases)
- NEVER mock the system under test — only mock external dependencies
- Tests MUST be in tests/unit/ or tests/integration/ folders
- ALWAYS run: pytest --cov=src --cov-fail-under=70 before committing

### Design Patterns
- Strategy Pattern is used for FineStrategy — ALWAYS add new fine algorithms as new Strategy classes
- Observer Pattern is used for notifications — ALWAYS use EventBus.publish_event() for domain events
- NEVER add direct notification calls inside services — use events only

### File Structure
- Models go in src/models/
- Services go in src/services/
- Repository implementations go in src/storage/
- Utilities go in src/utils/
- NEVER mix layers

### Forbidden
- External DB connections
- HTTP requests in business logic
- Hardcoded IDs
- Magic numbers without named constants
- Mutable default arguments in Python
